			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting...<a name="20112"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 04 6:39 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First of all, you're using Brusco's Boastful Bellow, which is a single target DD and not an ae dot, as well as Selo's Consonant Chain, which is a single target snare. The only ae dot you're using is Denon's Disruptive Discord, so it's no wonder they're staying that high in hp. You need to twist in all the ae dots you have at that level, which I believe is 2. You'll also want to use a percussion instrument to increase the damage of the dots. Finally, it would be wise to try and twist in selo's, as you'll be in trouble with just SoW if you get attacked by a lightcrawler.
<br />

<br />
Try having this setup: Selo's Accelerando, Chords of Dissonance, Denon's Disruptive Discord, Hymn of Restoration. Then grab all the Stonegrabbers you want, and twist the first three. If you get caught and lose some hitpoints, you can change and do a 1,2,4,1,3,4. Try also, if you're uncertain if you hit the mobs or not, to have a window up with just the spam, and look for a lot of messages with A Stonegrabber winces.
<br />

<br />
So in conclusion: you're doing too little damage. Mobs in Marus Seru have fairly high regeneration, so an instrument modifier is a must, as well as using both the dots at that level, instead of just one.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
