				<td colspan="2"><span>I know that several posts have mentinoed Marus Seru as an excellent place to ae kite, but I have the same problem as the original poster.  I use selos, CoD, DDD, and twist in Hymn if I'm banged up, and I have yet to actually finish any sizable kites before they get me low enough on HP that I decide to abort the kite.  I notice that if they aren't actually dotted for a round (like if I'm OOR on my circle, or have to skip couple rounds for Hymn) they regen REAL fast.
<br />

<br />
In contrast Iceclad cougars seem to not regen at all, in fact, on occasion I have died, come back, looted my body, and just resumed my kite, with the cougars still substantially hurt.
<br />

<br />
I've decided that M. Seru is not great UNLESS you have good instruments to boost your dots. I'm mostly untwinked and have just a standard horn and Lute of the Gypsy princess, and most of the time I have not been swapping the horn in, because I'm not that great at swapping while running in circles yet (still learning that one).
<br />

